uiten verübt worden sind. Dabei werden Muster von sexueller Gewalt deutlich, die sich auf spirituelle Bereiche ausdehnten, aber von den Ordensoberen nur in Extremfällen geahndet wurden. Dieser Ansatz ermöglicht es, ein neues Licht auf die Geschichte jesuitischer Bildungs- und Seelsorgeeinrichtungen zu werfen.  aThis study investigates sexual offenses that were committed in the early modern Jesuit order against school pupils, students, confessants, and other Jesuits. It reveals patterns of sexual violence that extended to spiritual fields but were only prosecuted by the heads of the order in extreme cases. This approach allows new light to be shed on the history of the institutions of Jesuit education and pastoral care.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aHomosexualität. 4aJesuiten. 4aPäderastie. 4aPädophilie. 4aSexualgeschichte. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aJesuits.  ahomosexuality.  apederasty.  apedophilia.  asexual history.0 cEPUBz97831113115550 cprintz978311131098540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111311142zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111311142zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111311142/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA